<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="37.[192,1440,916,977]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,916,942]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This is a slender species. The 
<typeStatus box="[659,757,916,942]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
is four times longer than broad. This characteristic will distinguish the 
<typeStatus box="[332,430,950,976]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen from specimens of other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1818" box="[829,896,950,976]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,896,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Axina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with a partial black pronotum midline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[191,1440,992,1256]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,992,1018]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[345,388,992,1018]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Size</emphasis>
. Length 12.0 mm; width 3.0 mm. 
<emphasis box="[777,835,993,1018]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[916,1008,992,1018]" captionStart="Figures 114–117" captionStartId="69.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@69.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="Figures 114–117. Habitus of Axina species. 114) Axina conspicua. 115) A. equestris. 116) A. ignota. 117) A. ordinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565039/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Fig. 117</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1019,1080,992,1018]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium, thorax, and legs castaneous, except, pronotum with narrow black line that extends from mesoscutellum to discal indentation; elytra bicolorous, mostly flavotestaceous, epipleural margin broadly dark brown, dark brown region projects laterally to occupy elytral base, elytron middle, and elytral preapical region. 
<emphasis box="[951,1009,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 45/10. 
<emphasis box="[781,859,1128,1154]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 paralateral spheroid tumescences, disc narrowly concave near middle; PW/PL 110/140; elytra, asetiferous punctures substriate, punctures extend posteriorly to elytral 3/4, width of interstitial spaces variable; EL/EW 410/90. 
<emphasis box="[1241,1347,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Female pygidium trilobed distally (
<figureCitation box="[496,577,1229,1256]" captionStart="Figures 56–57" captionStartId="51.[192,279,1523,1549]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,1091,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-63@51.[192,1440,1091,1493]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Figures 56–57. Female genitalia. 56) Axina ordinis. 57) A. basalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564987" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564987/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[192,970,1271,1298]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" type="distribution">
